					<description><![CDATA[<p>Ares Management Corporation (ARES) has successfully raised $12.7 billion over the last nine months for its asset-based finance strategy. The major focus of the fundraising is the first and final</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/ares-secures-12-7-billion-in-major-fundraising-push/" data-wpel-link="internal">Ares Secures $12.7 Billion in Major Fundraising Push</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.ares.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Ares Management Corporation</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> (ARES) has successfully raised $12.7 billion over the last nine months for its asset-based </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/minerva-raises-20m-to-transform-marketing-technology/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">finance </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">strategy. The major focus of the fundraising is the first and final close of Ares Pathfinder Fund III, which hit its increased hard cap of $8.5 billion in limited partner commitments. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Notably, the oversubscribed fund achieved this final close in less than six months following its official launch in January 2026. This rapid closing makes Pathfinder III the largest global asset-based finance fund currently in the market.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Stepping Into the Legacy Banking Vacuum</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Asset-based finance involves extending credit secured by pools of predictable, physical, or financial assets ranging from consumer auto loans and credit card receivables to corporate equipment leases, supply chain finance, and residential mortgages.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Historically, this massive market was dominated by traditional commercial banks. However, a combination of stricter regulatory capital mandates (such as Basel III regulations) and recent regional banking volatility has forced traditional lenders to shrink their balance sheets and retrench from complex lending.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_202752" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202752" class="size-large wp-image-202752" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/coins-in-a-jar-2-1024x683.jpg" alt="coins in a jar" width="1024" height="683" /><p id="caption-attachment-202752" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Private credit managers like Ares have enthusiastically stepped into this vacuum. </span>Unlike standard corporate direct lending, asset-based finance collateralizes loans against concrete assets, providing institutional investors with an extra layer of insulation.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;The speed and size of this fundraise underscore our investors&#8217; confidence in our team&#8217;s differentiated track record of sourcing and underwriting relative value investment opportunities in ABF,&#8221; said Joel Holsinger, co-head of Alternative Credit at Ares. &#8220;Bolstered by market volatility as well as our team&#8217;s expanded capabilities across sectors, we are energized by the growing opportunity set across the ABF market.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/minerva-raises-20m-to-transform-marketing-technology/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Minerva Raises $20M to Transform Marketing Technology</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Building a Massive Illiquid Credit Moat</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The Alternative Credit arm at Ares represents one of the industry&#8217;s most fortified operations, boasting 95 dedicated investment professionals. As of March 31, 2026, and factoring in the new capital, Ares Alternative Credit manages approximately $57.3 billion in assets.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Crucially, $33.1 billion of that pool is explicitly dedicated to non-investment-grade assets. Ares&#8217; senior leadership notes that this concentrated allocation represents the largest single pool of illiquid asset-based finance capital anywhere in the global market, allowing the firm to write massive, highly customised cheques that smaller competitors cannot match.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;We believe we have raised four of the five largest ABF funds in the market to date,&#8221; added Kevin Alexander, Co-Head of Alternative Credit at Ares. &#8220;This strengthens our ability to capitalize on the demand driven by current market conditions and deliver customizable liquidity solutions at scale.&#8221;</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Aligning Billions with Global Philanthropy</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">A distinct characteristic of the Pathfinder fund family is its integrated, structural tie-in to global philanthropy. Under the fund&#8217;s charter, Ares and the Pathfinder portfolio managers have pledged to donate between 5% and 10% of the carried interest profits directly to global health and education charitable organizations.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With the closing of Pathfinder III, the total pool of assets under management driving this philanthropic engine has climbed to approximately $28.7 billion. Based on fund performance data calculated through the first quarter of 2026, the Pathfinder vehicles have already accrued $56.9 million in pledged charitable contributions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This private credit philanthropic model has begun to reshape the wider asset-management landscape. In late 2025, Ares leveraged the momentum of this framework to help launch Promote Giving, an industry-wide initiative where participating asset managers commit to donating at least 5% of their performance fees to charity. The initiative has quickly scaled from eight founding firms to 13 major global participants.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The immense fundraising milestone brings Ares Management&#8217;s total global footprint to more than $644 billion in assets under management across its credit, real estate, private equity, and infrastructure divisions. At a time when the broader private credit market is navigating slower retail inflows and rising redemption questions, Ares&#8217; institutional fundraising engine shows zero signs of slowing down.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/ares-secures-12-7-billion-in-major-fundraising-push/" data-wpel-link="internal">Ares Secures $12.7 Billion in Major Fundraising Push</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
