					<description><![CDATA[<p>Evotrex Raises $30M to Accelerate Hybrid RV Production Evotrex has raised $30 million in Series A funding. The round included GSR United Capital, Forebright Concerto Capital, Unique Capital, Pegasus Capital,</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/evotrex-raises-30m-series-a-rv-development/" data-wpel-link="internal">Evotrex Raises $30M Series A to Advance Power-Generating RV Development</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Evotrex Raises $30M to Accelerate Hybrid RV Production</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Evotrex has raised $30 million in Series A funding. The round included GSR United Capital, Forebright Concerto Capital, Unique Capital, Pegasus Capital, TTGG Ventures, ChunJia Capital, and Thundersoft.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The latest investment brings total funding to $46 million. The Los Angeles-based company develops intelligent power-generating RV trailers designed for extended off-grid travel. Evotrex plans to use the capital to complete product development. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding will also support automotive-standard testing and validation. Production preparation for its flagship trailer is another key priority. The company emerged from stealth last year. It later introduced its first product at CES. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Management is now focused on moving the platform toward commercial production. Customer deliveries are expected to begin in 2027. Evotrex aims to produce approximately 1,000 units annually during its initial growth phase.</span></p>
<h2><b>PG5 Trailer Combines Mobility and Energy Independence</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company&#8217;s flagship product is the Evotrex-PG5. It is designed as a mobile energy platform rather than a traditional RV. The trailer combines battery power, solar energy, and onboard electricity generation.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">A large battery pack powers the system. Roof-mounted solar panels provide additional energy generation. An ultra-quiet petrol generator serves as a backup charging source. Unlike conventional hybrid vehicles, the engine does not directly drive the trailer. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Instead, it functions solely as a generator. This helps recharge the battery during extended off-grid travel. The PG5 also includes </span><a href="https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/thermal" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">thermal</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> efficiency features. Excess heat generated by the engine can be redirected to warm the living space. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This improves energy utilisation during colder conditions. Evotrex believes the design addresses limitations found in fully electric RVs. It aims to provide longer operating periods without requiring external charging infrastructure.</span></p>
<h2><b>Growing Demand Fuels Interest in Alternative RV Technology</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_202739" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202739" class="size-full wp-image-202739" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/create-a-futuristic-neon-lit-poster-with_i_epItGwVh6xo1wm96JJ8g_ZLVFHnx0QBahCwZPZ_vKqQ_cover.png" alt="Hybrid RV trailer with solar, battery, and generator system designed for off-grid energy independence" width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-202739" class="wp-caption-text">Rising demand for energy-independent travel drives interest in hybrid RV innovation as Evotrex gains momentum. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The recreational vehicle industry is undergoing significant change. Traditional manufacturers have been slower to introduce electric products. This has created opportunities for emerging technology-focused companies.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Several startups are developing battery-powered travel trailers. Evotrex has chosen a different approach through extended-range electric technology. The company believes this provides a practical balance between range and sustainability.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Interest from customers appears strong. According to the company, around 90% of current reservations are for the premium version of the PG5. The top-tier model is priced at approximately $160,000.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founder and CEO Alex Xiao said competition benefits the market. He believes growing awareness will help accelerate adoption of next-generation RV technologies. The company says its platform is built for users seeking greater travel flexibility. Off-grid capability remains one of the primary selling points.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company is also drawing on experience from the consumer electronics sector. Xiao previously worked at Anker. He credits product quality and customer satisfaction as important growth drivers.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Investors appear optimistic about the opportunity. Demand for innovative outdoor travel solutions continues to increase. Consumers are seeking greater independence and energy flexibility.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/alta-ares-raises-50m-air-defence-ai/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Alta Ares Raises €50M to Scale AI-Powered Air Defence Systems</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Testing and Customer Experience Remain Key Priorities</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Evotrex has already completed validation of a functional PG5 prototype. The company now plans an extensive testing programme. Durability and reliability remain critical objectives before launch.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Management expects testing to continue for the next 10 to 12 months. The goal is to ensure the vehicle performs reliably across different environments and conditions. Manufacturing will take place in China. Final assembly is expected to occur in California. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company is placing significant emphasis on customer support. Notably, its first service employee joined before its first sales employee. Leadership views long-term customer satisfaction as essential to growth.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Los Angeles remains central to the company&#8217;s strategy. The region provides access to target customers and diverse testing environments. Different climates can help validate product performance before launch.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With fresh capital secured, Evotrex is entering a crucial development phase. The company aims to establish itself within the evolving RV market through innovative energy technology and a strong focus on customer experience. Evotrex is currently finalising production locations for both operations.</span></p>
