										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>CameraMatics Raises €49M to Accelerate Global Expansion</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">CameraMatics has raised up to €49 million in new funding. The investment was led by Blume Equity. The Ireland Strategic Investment Fund and Goodbody Capital Partners also participated. The funding will support the company&#8217;s next stage of growth. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">CameraMatics plans to expand across North America and mainland Europe. It will also strengthen enterprise sales and customer success operations. Founded in Ireland in 2016, CameraMatics develops AI-powered fleet intelligence technology. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Its platform helps commercial fleet operators improve safety, reduce operational risk, and lower emissions. The company combines video telematics, driver assistance systems, and real-time analytics.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The investment also delivers returns for existing </span><a href="https://www.collinsdictionary.com/dictionary/english/investor" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">investors</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. Mindflair expects to receive €600,000 in cash proceeds from the transaction. Despite the repayment, it will continue to retain exposure to CameraMatics through Sure Valley Ventures&#8217; first fund.</span></p>
<h2><b>AI Fleet Platform Gains Momentum Across International Markets</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">CameraMatics has experienced strong growth in recent years. The company now serves nearly 1,000 fleet customers. Its technology supports thousands of commercial vehicles across the UK, Ireland, Europe, and the United States.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform uses AI-powered video intelligence to monitor fleet activity. It helps operators identify risks before incidents occur. The technology also improves compliance with evolving industry regulations.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Enterprise adoption continues to accelerate. Recent contract wins include Royal Mail, Calor Gas, Wolseley, XPO, and DFDS. In the United States, the company has expanded through deployments with Installed Building Products.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">CameraMatics expects contracted recurring revenue to exceed €30 million this year. Growth has been driven by increasing demand for safety, compliance, and operational efficiency tools. Logistics, infrastructure, and utility operators remain key customer groups.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company continues to invest in machine learning and predictive safety technology. Its long-term goal is to eliminate driving and workplace accidents through connected fleet intelligence.</span></p>
<h2><b>Investors Back Growing Demand for Connected Fleet Technology<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_202715" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202715" class="size-full wp-image-202715" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/a-futuristic-poster-showcases-a-dynamic-_iGz8pJKBVruOCivb08VYxg_oTHUdPa_RLuRRu6mM9MI8w.png" alt="AI-driven fleet intelligence system with connected vehicles, predictive safety analytics, and real-time telematics monitoring." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-202715" class="wp-caption-text">Investor confidence grows in AI fleet technology as CameraMatics strengthens its position in connected transport intelligence. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The investment is indicative of growing confidence in AI powered transportation solutions. The investors see opportunity in connected fleet management solutions, which is growing thanks to increased safety regulations and demands for a greener operation.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Blume Equity sees a great opportunity for the company, in expanding to further international markets. Blume noted CameraMatics&#8217; strong customer relations, unique technology, and an increase in its enterprise presence.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The fleet intelligence market is at the threshold of a new period of growth. Companies are increasingly taking advantage of video telematics for better driver behavior and decreased insurance prices. The AI powered information will play a growing part in future fleet management.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">CameraMatics has secured its place as a category leader. Its combination of safety technologies and operational analytics is fueling its sustained growth and customers acquisition.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/gt-medical-raises-100m-series-e/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">GT Medical Technologies Raises $100M Series E to Advance Brain Tumour Therapy</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Expansion Strategy Focuses on AI Innovation and Enterprise Growth</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">New investment is expected to speed up product development. CameraMatics will continue to reinvest heavily in AI capability and green-innovation. In addition, will look to invest in the connected fleet intelligence platform.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The management sees major opportunities across a variety of markets around the world. The appetite for AI solutions in fleet management continues to grow; and organisations are looking to increase operational insight and safety performance.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Co-founders Mervyn O&#8217;Callaghan and Simon Murray remain committed to the long-term leadership and vision of the business, in growing CameraMatics globally and building on technology.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The firm has over 150 staff located in Ireland, Britain and across three locations in Europe and two in the USA. The expansion is expected to offer the possibility of new jobs in the aforementioned areas of operation.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The belief that AI is an area where road safety could be further improved is a core part of CameraMatics’ objectives; the new funding will help accelerate its mission of saving lives and lowering the risk profile for vehicles around the world, allowing the firm to begin the next phase of global growth.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/cameramatics-raises-49m-ai-fleet-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal">CameraMatics Raises €49M to Expand AI Fleet Intelligence Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
