					<description><![CDATA[<p>Element Biosciences reported that it has closed an upsized Series E funding round. A headline in the round was a huge $175 million strategic investment from longtime backer Samsung Electronics.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/element-biosciences-raises-175m-for-gene-sequencing/" data-wpel-link="internal">Element Biosciences Raises $175M for Gene Sequencing</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.elementbiosciences.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Element Biosciences</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> reported that it has closed an upsized Series E </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/morpho-raises-175-million-to-expand-defi-lending/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round. A headline in the round was a huge $175 million strategic investment from longtime backer Samsung Electronics.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new investment means that Samsung will be the largest shareholder in the San Diego-based biotech company. This newest round of investment comes on the back of a Series D financing in July 2024, in which Element raised $277 million and signals quick momentum as the company looks to go head-to-head with well-established industry leaders.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Cracking the Multiomics Frontier</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Element Biosciences, founded in 2017, has been able to steadily grow market share by reducing the financial and technological barriers for high-precision genetic testing. Its proprietary DNA sequencing platforms reached an accuracy of 99.99% while simultaneously reducing costs for lab researchers.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_202705" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202705" class="size-large wp-image-202705" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/blue-and-white-spirals-1024x576.jpg" alt="blue and white spirals" width="1024" height="576" /><p id="caption-attachment-202705" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In addition to high-precision DNA sequencing, Element has emerged as a leader in multiomics. This highly advanced cross-disciplinary approach provides a single hardware setup for cell biologists to analyse DNA, RNA, and proteins in parallel rather than investing in multiple specialised lab tools. This multidimensional approach of encoding biological information offers scientists a look at exactly how genetic information translates into cell variations over time, providing insights necessary to develop advanced therapies for cancer medications.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/morpho-raises-175-million-to-expand-defi-lending/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Morpho Raises $175 Million to Expand DeFi Lending</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Scaling the Platform Ecosystem</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new funding will be used to expand Element&#8217;s commercial presence for its evolving family of instruments worldwide. The company&#8217;s commercial efforts are currently focused on its popular AVITI benchtop sequencing system and recently debuted AVITI 24 for multiomic and cellular time course analysis.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company has subsequently announced its funds are also to be used to commercialise its next generation of hardware, VITARI and AVITI Dx. VITARI is a high-output model designed to increase analysis throughput 5-fold with a &gt;50% reduction in data generation costs relative to previous generation products. AVITI Dx will be the company&#8217;s dedicated clinical diagnostics platform, designed specifically to be adopted by hospital laboratories to inform hyper-personalised drug regimens for oncology patients.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Thus far, Element has deployed its platforms in over 40 countries, across a range of academic, pharma, and clinical research institutions.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Samsung Synergy and Healthcare AI</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The investment crowns Samsung as the largest equity holder, but Element will maintain its existing management and operations structure. The deeper tie-up seeks to develop an interoperable technology alliance by cross-pollinating Element&#8217;s genomic architectures with Samsung&#8217;s formidable industrial real estate base in AI, consumer electronics, and digital medical systems.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Samsung will leverage its Caffeine deep learning models and big data backbone to substantially improve the genomics data rate, pushing massive, complex biological data sets much closer to a live interactive analysis. The electronics heavyweight also envisions a multi-year consumer healthcare crossover, where over time its daily biometric input comes from commercial wearables such as the Galaxy Watch and Galaxy Ring, which is linked to users&#8217; genomic blueprints to create a mobile-centric preventative medicine and early detection paradigm. </span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/element-biosciences-raises-175m-for-gene-sequencing/" data-wpel-link="internal">Element Biosciences Raises $175M for Gene Sequencing</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
